{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Amos

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1 }The message of Amos, one of the sheep breeders of Tekoa, which he saw concerning Israel in the reign of King Uzziah of Judah, and in the reign of Jeroboam the son of King Joash of Israel, two years before the earthquake. {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2} Amos said:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 Whenever the {\scaps Lord} roars from Zion,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and utters his voice from Jerusalem,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 the pastures of the shepherds dry up,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 the top of Carmel becomes arid.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 God\uc1\u8217*s Judgment on Israel\uc1\u8217*s Neighbors

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3} The {\scaps Lord} says:
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 For Damascus\uc1\u8217* three crimes \uc1\u8211* no, four! \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 I will not rescind my judgment.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 They have threshed Gilead
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 with threshing instruments of iron.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4} Therefore I will send fire on Hazael\uc1\u8217*s house,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 it will devour the palaces of Ben-hadad.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5} I will break open the gate of Damascus,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 I will wipe out those who live in the valley of Aven
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and the sceptered ruler of Beth-Eden.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 The people of Aram will go into captivity in Kir,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6} The {\scaps Lord} says:
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 For Gaza\uc1\u8217*s three crimes \uc1\u8211* no, four! \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 I will not rescind my judgment.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 They carried away captive a whole nation,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 sold them as slaves to Edom.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7} Therefore I will send fire on the wall of Gaza,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and it will devour her palaces.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8} And I will wipe out those who live in Ashdod,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and the sceptered ruler of Askelon.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 I will turn my hand against Ekron,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and the remnant of the Philistines will perish,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9} The {\scaps Lord} says:
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 For Tyre\uc1\u8217*s three crimes \uc1\u8211* no, four! \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 I will not rescind my judgment.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 They carried away captive a whole people into exile in Edom,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and did not remember the brotherly covenant.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10} So I will send fire on the walls of Tyre.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 It will devour her palaces.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11} The {\scaps Lord} says:
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 For Edom\uc1\u8217*s three crimes \uc1\u8211* no, four! \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 I will not rescind my judgment.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 They pursued their relatives with the sword,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 stilled their pity,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 cherished their anger continually,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 retained their fury forever.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12} So I will send a fire into Teman.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 It will destroy the palaces of Bozrah.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13} The {\scaps Lord} says:
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 For Ammonites\uc1\u8217* three crimes \uc1\u8211* no, four! \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 I will not rescind my judgment.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 They have ripped open pregnant women in Gilead,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 in their lust for land.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14} So I will kindle a fire on the wall of Rabbah.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 It will destroy her palaces,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 with a war-cry in the day of battle,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 with a tempest in the day of the whirlwind.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15} Their king will go into exile,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 he and his nobles together,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 2 }The {\scaps Lord} says:
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 For Moab\uc1\u8217*s three crimes \uc1\u8211* no, four! \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 I will not rescind my judgment.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 They have burned to lime the bones of the king of Edom,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2} to desecrate the dead.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 So I will send a fire into Moab.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 It will devour the palaces of Kirioth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 with a war-cry,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 with the sound of trumpets.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3} I will kill the ruler,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 all his nobles I will slay with him,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4} The {\scaps Lord} says:
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 For Judah\uc1\u8217*s three crimes \uc1\u8211* no, four! \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 I will not rescind my judgment.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 They have rejected the law of the {\scaps Lord}
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and have not kept his statutes.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 Instead their false gods their ancestors followed,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 have led them astray.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5} So I will send a fire on Judah.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 It will devour the palaces of Jerusalem.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 God\uc1\u8217*s Judgment on Israel

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6} The {\scaps Lord} says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 For Israel\uc1\u8217*s three crimes \uc1\u8211* no, four! \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 I will not rescind my judgment.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 They sell the righteous for money,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 the needy for a pair of shoes.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7} They trample on the head of the poor,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 push the humble out of the way.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 Father and son go to the same temple girl,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and so profane my holy name.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8} They stretch themselves
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 on garments taken in pledges beside every altar,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and they drink the wine
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 of those who have been fined in the house of their God.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9} It was I who destroyed the Amorites for your sake,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 whose height was like that of the cedars,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 as strong as oaks.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 I destroyed their fruit from above
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and their roots from below.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10} It was I who brought you up from the land of Egypt,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 led you forty years in the wilderness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 brought you here to possess the land of the Amorites.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11} I raised up some of your sons to be prophets
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 some of your youths to be Nazirites.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 Is not this indeed so, Israelites?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12} But you made the Nazirites drink wine
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and banned the prophets from prophesying.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13} Listen!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 It is I who will make you groan in your places,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 as a wagon groans under its load of grain.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14} Then flight will fail the swift,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and the strength of the strongest will be useless.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 The warrior will not save his life,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15} the archer will not stand firm,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 the swift of foot will not escape,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 the horseman will not save his life.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16} The bravest of warriors
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 will flee away naked in that day,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 A Warning to Israel

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 3 }Listen to this message, Israelites,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 which the {\scaps Lord} has spoken against you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 against the whole nation that I brought out of Egypt:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2} You alone have I cared for of all the nations of the world,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 this is why I will punish you for your crimes.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3} Do two walk together
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 unless they agreed to meet?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4} Does a lion roar in the forest
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 when there is no prey for him?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 Does a young lion cry out in his den
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 unless he has caught something?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5} Does a bird swoop down into a trap
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 if no bait is set for it?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 Does a trap spring up from the ground
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 if nothing sets it off?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6} Can a trumpet be blown in a city
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and the people not tremble?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 Can disaster strike a city
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and the {\scaps Lord} not have caused it?
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7} Surely the Lord {\scaps God} does nothing
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 without revealing his purpose to his servants the prophets.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8} The lion has roared; who does not fear?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 The Lord {\scaps God} has spoken; who will not prophesy?
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9} Proclaim over the palaces in Ashdod,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and over the palaces in the land of Egypt:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 Gather upon the mountain of Samaria,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and see the violent turmoil,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 the acts of oppression in her midst.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10} For they do not know how to do right.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 They are heaping up violence
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and oppression in their palaces,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11} Therefore the Lord {\scaps God} says:
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 An enemy will surround the land,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 he will strip your strength from you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and your palaces will be looted.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12} The {\scaps Lord} says:
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 Just as a shepherd rescues from the jaws of a lion
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 two shinbones or a piece of an ear,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 so the Israelites living in Sameria will be rescued \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 with the corner of a couch,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and the damask of a divan!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13} Listen and testify against the house of Jacob,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 says the Lord {\scaps God}, the God of hosts.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14} On the day when I punish Israel for their crimes,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 I will also visit in judgment the altars of Bethel,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 the horns of the altar will be hacked off,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and they will fall to the ground.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15} I will destroy the winter houses
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 together with the summer houses
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 and the houses of ivory will perish.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 Many great houses will be swept away,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 4 }Listen to this message, women of Sameria,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 you well-fed cows of Bashan,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 who oppress the poor and crush the needy,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 who say to your husbands, \uc1\u8220*Bring us another drink!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2} The Lord {\scaps God} has sworn by his holiness:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 The time is coming when you will be carried away in baskets,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 your children carried away in fish-baskets,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3} and through the breaches in the city wall you will go,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 thrown out on the garbage dump,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

